File: The fire gutted dozens of structures built inside and around the abandoned factory. (AFP) JOHANNESBURG - Cape Town firefighters battled to put out a strong blaze on Thursday. The fire broke out at the Table Mountain National Park. READ: Diepsloot blaze contained but still burning: Joburg EMS The City's Fire and Rescue Service along with national park teams managed to contain the blaze. A strong south-easterly wind forced two helicopters to be deployed with water buckets to douse the flames. Several roads near Camps Bay were closed but no damage to property was reported.